
uss, UpStream Scripts
Scripts for upstream, will not go into `make dist`-tarballs.

Name convention: all lower case, non hyphe, no underscore.

From toplevel directory you can say: `uss/scriptname`.


Available scripts:
==================

* autogen.sh
Run autogen.sh with the preferred options of upstream programmers

* genreadme
Generates the README file.

* mkcvstarball
A `make dist` plus some hacks to have allways a working `make dist`

* ckgtkdocincludes
Checks that all the header files have corresponding xi:includes
in doc/reference/conglomerate-docs.sgml

* mkgtkdoctypes
Generates doc/reference/conglomerate.types - input file for gtk-doc

* mkgtkdocoverrides
Generates doc/reference/conglomerate-overrides.txt - input file for gtk-doc

* mkgtkdocsections
Updates doc/reference/conglomerate-sections.txt - input file for gtk-doc

* mkgtkdoc
Calls the mkgtkdoc*s scripts

* mkpotfilesin
Makes a new po/POTFILES.in, run this script once in a while.
It will update also the po/ChangeLog and ask for a CVS commit.

* updateconfigsubguess
Wget config.sub and config.gues from GNU.
To keep these files up to date.

* wgetspec
Web get the spec file that Dag Wieers provides.
